{
  "uuid": "bbf49c0f4e5bac0d16416262494a10d7",
  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Ocean Freight BD Manager",
  "description": "<h2>Responsibilities</h2><ul><li><p>Identify and develop new business opportunities to drive revenue growth, with a primary focus on <strong>Ocean Freight forwarding</strong> in <strong>Singapore and Malaysia</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Lead, manage, and mentor the <strong>Sales team across the SEA region</strong>, including Vietnam, Malaysia, Singapore, Thailand, Indonesia, and Australia.</p></li><li><p>Drive both <strong>short-term and long-term sales targets</strong>, with performance evaluated based on <strong>half-yearly revenue and profit generation</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Actively engage potential and existing clients by providing tailored <strong>freight forwarding solutions</strong>, primarily in ocean freight.</p></li><li><p>Acquire new customers while maintaining strong relationships with existing clients through <strong>customer retention, cross-selling, and upselling</strong> initiatives.</p></li><li><p>Collaborate closely with the <strong>Pricing team</strong> to stay updated on ocean freight market trends, rates, and capacity in order to secure competitive pricing and space with carriers.</p></li><li><p>Manage and develop <strong>large-scale, long-term contracts</strong> and global accounts.</p></li><li><p>Prepare, report, and present <strong>sales performance updates</strong> during internal management meetings.</p></li></ul><h2>Requirements</h2><h3>Education</h3><ul><li><p>Bachelor’s degree or above in <strong>Business Administration, Transportation, Logistics, Supply Chain Management</strong>, or a related discipline.</p></li><li><p>Proficient in speaking, additional language skills are an advantage. </p></li></ul><h3>Experience</h3><ul><li><p>Minimum <strong>10 years of experience</strong> in the logistics industry, with a strong focus on <strong>Ocean Freight forwarding</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Proven track record in <strong>new business development and sales account acquisition</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Experience working in a <strong>global or top-tier freight forwarding company</strong> is highly preferred.</p></li><li><p>Demonstrated experience in managing <strong>large-scale, long-term contracts</strong> and <strong>global accounts</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Strong <strong>customer network</strong> in <strong>Southeast Asia and Australia</strong> is an advantage.</p></li></ul>",
